== Commands ==

* add <task>				add task
* append <ID> <task>		add <task> to the end of item <ID>
* replace <ID> <task>		replace item <ID> with <task>
* pri <ID> <priority>		set <priority> for item <ID>
* do <ID>					mark item <ID> as completed
* rm <ID>					delete item <ID>

* list [<terms>]			display all items containing <terms>, sorted by priority
* listpri [<priority>]		display all items with priority <priority>

* archive					move completed items from the list of active items to the archive
* remdup					remove duplicates from the list of active items

* report					add the number of active and completed items to the report

Aliases:
* a		add
* p		pri
* ls	list
* lsp	listpri

Legend:
* <ID>				task ID (any integer)
* <task>			task-description string (can contain nanoformats like priority, project, context etc.)
* <priority>		task priority (any uppercase Latin letter; A-Z)
* <terms>			space-separated list of filter terms
* [...]				optional argument

== Options ==

* -c <filepath>		custom configuration file
* -p				plain mode (no colored output)

== Configuration Settings ==

* base dir (for local storage)
* colored output
* priority colors
* use UTC
* flag char and timestamp
